WEBVTT

1
00:04:20.345 --> 00:04:23.015
You are confused. aren't you? Frightened.

2
00:04:23.140 --> 00:04:25.976
- That's alright. I can help you.
- Who is this?

3
00:04:26.101 --> 00:04:27.811
I am a doctor. Now. you must listen to me.

4
00:04:27.936 --> 00:04:30.439
You have lost your memory.
There was an experiment.

5
00:04:30.564 --> 00:04:33.734
Something went wrong. Your memory
was erased. Do you understand me?

6
00:04:33.859 --> 00:04:35.694
I don't understand.
What the hell is going on here?

7
00:04:35.819 --> 00:04:38.655
Just listen. There are people
coming for you even as we speak.

8
00:04:38.781 --> 00:04:42.201
<i>You must not let them find you. You must leave now.</i>

9
00:04:42.326 --> 00:04:44.870
Hello? Are you there?

10
00:05:43.637 --> 00:05:48.433
Hey. Mr. Murdoch. the Automat called.
said you left your wallet there.

11
00:05:49.434 --> 00:05:52.521
I suggest you retrieve it
since you only paid for three weeks.

12
00:05:52.646 --> 00:05:54.648
and they was up ten minutes ago.

13
00:05:56.275 --> 00:05:58.193
I've been here three weeks?

14
00:05:58.318 --> 00:06:01.280
It's right there in black and white. Mr. Murdoch.

15
00:06:01.405 --> 00:06:03.156
Day and date.

16
00:06:03.824 --> 00:06:07.077
We make our books like
we make our beds. all neat and tidy.

17
00:06:07.202 --> 00:06:09.955
- I'll take care of it when I get back.
- See that you do.

18
00:06:10.080 --> 00:06:13.834
Only thing makes you a guest in this joint.
pal. is cash on the barrel head!

19
00:06:37.733 --> 00:06:40.319
House rules. Three weeks is three weeks.

20
00:06:40.444 --> 00:06:42.863
No days off for good behavior.

21
00:07:05.010 --> 00:07:08.680
Mr. Murdoch. yes. where is he?

22
00:07:08.805 --> 00:07:12.351
He just left not five minutes ago.

23
00:07:15.562 --> 00:07:17.397
Sleep now.

24
00:07:57.813 --> 00:07:59.564
Hey. sweetie!

25
00:07:59.690 --> 00:08:03.694
He said he was your husband's doctor.
He wanted to speak with you.

26
00:08:23.714 --> 00:08:25.340
Excuse me.

27
00:08:26.675 --> 00:08:30.887
- Dr. Sh...
- Schreber. Please. won't you come in?

28
00:08:31.013 --> 00:08:33.015
You must be Emma Murdoch.

29
00:08:33.849 --> 00:08:36.893
Thank you for coming to see me
on such short notice.

30
00:08:38.937 --> 00:08:41.189
What is this?

31
00:08:41.314 --> 00:08:45.318
A rather crude experiment.
designed to further my studies.

32
00:08:45.444 --> 00:08:49.072
I don't understand.
you say you're my husband's doctor.

33
00:08:49.197 --> 00:08:51.408
but he never mentioned you to me.

34
00:08:51.533 --> 00:08:52.951
The truth is. Mrs. Murdoch.

35
00:08:53.076 --> 00:08:55.787
John has been coming to see me
for quite some time.

36
00:08:55.912 --> 00:08:59.416
He had been grappling
with feelings of betrayal.

37
00:08:59.541 --> 00:09:02.669
stemming from your marital difficulties.

38
00:09:02.794 --> 00:09:05.005
- John told you what happened?
- Yes.

39
00:09:06.048 --> 00:09:08.258
When was the last time that you saw him?

40
00:09:08.383 --> 00:09:09.801
Three weeks ago.

41
00:09:09.926 --> 00:09:13.555
He packed a suitcase.
He was very angry at me.

42
00:09:13.680 --> 00:09:16.600
I understand how difficult
this must be for you.

43
00:09:16.725 --> 00:09:20.729
But for John's sake. I would like you
to think of me as your friend. Emma.

44
00:09:20.854 --> 00:09:24.524
It appears that John has suffered
a psychotic break.

45
00:09:24.649 --> 00:09:26.777
Complete memory loss.

46
00:09:27.736 --> 00:09:30.989
He may be delusional. Even violent.

47
00:09:31.740 --> 00:09:37.579
Emma. if he were to contact you.
and I suspect he will.

48
00:09:37.704 --> 00:09:40.499
you must call me immediately.
do you understand?

49
00:09:40.624 --> 00:09:43.960
It is imperative that
I be the first one to reach him.

50
00:09:44.836 --> 00:09:48.840
Wherever your husband is. he is searching...

51
00:09:48.965 --> 00:09:51.093
for himself.

52
00:10:02.104 --> 00:10:06.942
Good evening. Mr. Murdoch.
It is Mr. Murdoch. isn't it?

53
00:10:07.067 --> 00:10:10.862
Mr... Was it J-something-Murdoch?

54
00:10:14.032 --> 00:10:17.953
J. Murdoch. What's your name? Justin? Jerry?

55
00:10:19.246 --> 00:10:20.664
No.

56
00:10:22.290 --> 00:10:24.334
My name's Jason Murdoch. John Murdoch.

57
00:10:24.459 --> 00:10:27.003
Jake Murdoch. How's it going?
Hi. Jack Murdoch.

58
00:10:30.423 --> 00:10:31.675
Hi.

59
00:11:11.089 --> 00:11:12.507
Bumstead.

60
00:11:14.301 --> 00:11:17.262
I told the guy. "Cash on the barrel head."

61
00:11:17.387 --> 00:11:20.765
I said. "Listen. three weeks is three weeks."

62
00:11:20.891 --> 00:11:25.061
- Where's our lucky winner?
- Upstairs. sir. room... 614.

63
00:11:25.187 --> 00:11:27.022
Another call girl.

64
00:11:28.315 --> 00:11:31.526
J. Murdoch.

65
00:11:31.651 --> 00:11:34.696
- Evening. Husselbeck.
- Inspector Bumstead.

66
00:11:34.821 --> 00:11:38.200
- Your lace is untied.
- Sir.

67
00:11:49.628 --> 00:11:51.379
Am I glad you're here. sir.

68
00:11:51.504 --> 00:11:54.007
They say Detective Walenski's
got the heebie-jeebies.

69
00:11:54.132 --> 00:11:56.343
Just take what they give me. Husselbeck.

70
00:12:03.266 --> 00:12:07.520
Looks like somebody woke up
on the wrong side of the bed.

71
00:12:50.647 --> 00:12:53.149
- Hello?
- Oh. it's you.

72
00:12:53.275 --> 00:12:55.902
- You left your wallet here. buddy.
- When did I do that?

73
00:12:56.027 --> 00:12:58.071
- When you was last here.
- When was that?

74
00:12:58.196 --> 00:13:02.033
When you left your wallet.
You expect me to remember?

75
00:13:04.911 --> 00:13:08.999
Hello? Excuse me.

76
00:13:09.124 --> 00:13:11.793
No. no. seriously.

77
00:13:13.837 --> 00:13:15.255
Is it alleged?

78
00:13:29.352 --> 00:13:31.313
- Where you headed. chief?
- Home.

79
00:13:31.438 --> 00:13:32.689
And where's home?

80
00:13:32.814 --> 00:13:35.483
Haven't you mugs got anything better to do?

81
00:13:35.608 --> 00:13:37.777
Well. I'm just trying to do my job. May.

82
00:13:37.902 --> 00:13:39.904
There's a killer out there.
in case you hadn't noticed.

83
00:13:40.030 --> 00:13:43.450
Maybe you should be out looking for him.
instead of cooling your heels?

84
00:13:45.702 --> 00:13:47.662
Ah. go on. get out of here.

85
00:13:55.920 --> 00:13:57.005
Come on.

86
00:13:58.048 --> 00:14:00.592
Round and round she goes.

87
00:14:02.886 --> 00:14:07.015
Where she stops? Nobody knows.

88
00:14:09.976 --> 00:14:12.937
What's that make so far. Husselbeck?
Six hookers in all?

89
00:14:13.063 --> 00:14:16.900
- I believe so. sir.
- Give the man an "A" for effort.

90
00:14:17.025 --> 00:14:19.027
You'd think these stiffs would have the good grace

91
00:14:19.152 --> 00:14:21.780
to expire at a good time of night.

92
00:14:22.530 --> 00:14:24.783
Hey. too bad about Walenski?

93
00:14:28.119 --> 00:14:29.954
I guess he'd seen enough.

94
00:14:37.087 --> 00:14:39.089
So. Husselbeck...

95
00:14:39.214 --> 00:14:45.845
what kind of killer do you think
stops to save a dying fish?

96
00:14:45.970 --> 00:14:49.057
- You got me. sir.
- Bumstead. what took you?

97
00:14:49.182 --> 00:14:51.935
This killer's been running circles
around us. thanks to Walenski.

98
00:14:52.060 --> 00:14:53.770
With all due respect. Chief Inspector.

99
00:14:53.895 --> 00:14:57.190
I've known Eddie a long time. he's a good cop.

100
00:14:57.315 --> 00:15:01.444
Whatever kind of cop Walenski once was.
he let drift a long time ago.

101
00:15:01.569 --> 00:15:04.406
- Let me talk to Bumstead!
- Come on. let's go!

102
00:15:04.531 --> 00:15:07.200
- Hold on!
- Frank! Frank!

103
00:15:08.535 --> 00:15:10.703
Get his arm!

104
00:15:10.829 --> 00:15:12.831
- They're watching us!
- On your feet.

105
00:15:12.956 --> 00:15:16.000
- There's no way out!
- Don't make us hurt you.

106
00:15:16.126 --> 00:15:17.752
God. can't you see?

107
00:15:21.172 --> 00:15:23.967
Let me go. let me go!
I'm not gonna hurt you. I'm not...

108
00:15:24.926 --> 00:15:27.262
- What was that?
- Walenski.

109
00:15:35.687 --> 00:15:38.773
I'm being punished for my sins. right?

110
00:15:38.898 --> 00:15:42.318
What did I ever do to inherit this?
Where do you begin?

111
00:15:43.069 --> 00:15:47.282
Well. everything Detective Walenski
committed to paper should be here. so...

112
00:15:47.407 --> 00:15:50.910
The only thing that should be committed
is Walenski.

113
00:15:52.579 --> 00:15:55.623
Nothing like a little healthy paranoia.

114
00:15:58.251 --> 00:16:00.712
Sir. we just got the fingerprint results in.

115
00:16:04.674 --> 00:16:06.676
What is this. some kind of joke?

116
00:16:10.805 --> 00:16:12.807
Don't throw anything away.

117
00:16:18.146 --> 00:16:19.522
Inspector Bumstead.

118
00:16:21.649 --> 00:16:24.527
I came here to file a missing persons
report for my husband.

119
00:16:24.652 --> 00:16:29.073
- Take it to the front desk.
- They told me to come see you.

120
00:16:30.867 --> 00:16:32.869
His name's John Murdoch.

121
00:16:34.120 --> 00:16:37.415
Mrs. Murdoch. why didn't you report this before?

122
00:16:37.540 --> 00:16:42.295
If your husband has been missing
as long as you say...

123
00:16:42.420 --> 00:16:44.672
I thought he'd simply walked out on me.

124
00:16:46.007 --> 00:16:49.344
Then a doctor contacted me this evening.

125
00:16:50.303 --> 00:16:53.223
- How long have you been married?
- Nearly four years.

126
00:16:53.348 --> 00:16:55.892
Why do you ask?

127
00:16:56.017 --> 00:16:58.853
Because you seem uncomfortable with your ring.

128
00:16:58.978 --> 00:17:02.315
As if you were... unaccustomed to wearing it.

129
00:17:02.440 --> 00:17:04.484
I never take it off.

130
00:17:10.782 --> 00:17:14.118
Do these names mean anything to you?

131
00:17:20.291 --> 00:17:22.335
No. Who are these women?

132
00:17:23.169 --> 00:17:27.257
Why are you looking for my husband?
Are you going to accuse him of something?

133
00:17:27.382 --> 00:17:29.842
Maybe. Maybe murder.

134
00:17:29.968 --> 00:17:32.262
Whose murder?

135
00:17:32.387 --> 00:17:36.015
- Which one?
- All of them.

136
00:17:36.975 --> 00:17:40.144
Mrs. Murdoch. I am sorry.
I'm sorry. I didn't mean to alarm you.

137
00:17:40.270 --> 00:17:42.647
I'm sorry that I came.
Just both made a mistake.

138
00:17:42.772 --> 00:17:44.399
Mrs. Murdoch. if you please.

139
00:17:44.524 --> 00:17:46.859
If you'll just give me half a second to explain...

140
00:17:48.945 --> 00:17:51.197
I'll be right out.

141
00:18:15.430 --> 00:18:17.682
Have we met before?

142
00:18:17.807 --> 00:18:21.352
If we did. I hope you're still breathing.

143
00:18:21.477 --> 00:18:24.647
What's your name. honey?

144
00:18:24.772 --> 00:18:28.568
- John.
- Well. that's an appropriate name.

145
00:18:29.944 --> 00:18:31.571
Yeah.

146
00:18:36.451 --> 00:18:38.328
I was just thinking...

147
00:18:41.831 --> 00:18:43.583
What you do...

148
00:18:44.667 --> 00:18:49.547
seems kind of dangerous. right now.

149
00:18:49.672 --> 00:18:51.924
I mean. how do you know I'm not the killer?

150
00:18:52.050 --> 00:18:55.136
You don't seem like the killer type. Why?

151
00:18:56.387 --> 00:18:58.890
You feeling any urges I should know about?

152
00:19:20.161 --> 00:19:21.996
Ah. shoot.

153
00:20:20.388 --> 00:20:24.392
So. it seems you've discovered your unpleasant nature.

154
00:20:27.603 --> 00:20:32.316
- Who are you?
- We might ask the same question. yes?

155
00:20:32.442 --> 00:20:34.944
Sleep now.

156
00:21:01.345 --> 00:21:03.973
He can tune!

157
00:21:55.650 --> 00:21:58.861
What is to be done? This man is dangerous.

158
00:21:58.986 --> 00:22:02.406
- It is said he is able to tune.
- Impossible.

159
00:22:02.532 --> 00:22:05.243
We have seen it with our own eyes.

160
00:22:05.368 --> 00:22:07.787
On occasion. the imprinting does not take.

161
00:22:07.912 --> 00:22:10.456
They behave erratically when they awaken.

162
00:22:10.581 --> 00:22:14.126
We find them wandering like lost children.

163
00:22:14.252 --> 00:22:16.587
But this one was different. yes?

164
00:22:16.712 --> 00:22:20.341
- What has the Doctor to say about this?
- He has failed to report in.

165
00:22:20.466 --> 00:22:23.511
- And Mr. Quick?
- No more Mr. Quick.

166
00:22:23.636 --> 00:22:26.305
Mr. Quick. dead. yes.

167
00:22:29.350 --> 00:22:32.186
Poor. poor Mr. Quick.

168
00:22:32.311 --> 00:22:35.106
Mr. Book. does he know?

169
00:22:36.482 --> 00:22:39.026
Should we not know. Mr. Hand?

170
00:22:39.151 --> 00:22:42.113
We had hoped to learn more
before sharing with you.

171
00:22:42.238 --> 00:22:45.074
We can know nothing until we possess him.

172
00:22:45.992 --> 00:22:48.703
Mr. Night. you will take the East.

173
00:22:48.828 --> 00:22:51.247
Mr. Face. you the West.

174
00:22:51.372 --> 00:22:53.374
Mr. Glove. the South.

175
00:22:53.499 --> 00:22:55.960
Mr. Shade. the North.

176
00:22:57.545 --> 00:23:00.464
We must have this man.

177
00:23:13.978 --> 00:23:19.108
Do you really think my husband could be
capable of committing those murders?

178
00:23:19.233 --> 00:23:20.735
Do you?

179
00:23:22.445 --> 00:23:25.031
Let's hope. for both our sakes. that I'm wrong.

180
00:23:54.060 --> 00:23:55.603
John?

181
00:24:09.909 --> 00:24:12.078
I've been so worried about you.

182
00:24:15.539 --> 00:24:17.583
Are you punishing me?

183
00:24:17.708 --> 00:24:21.253
You know. if disappearing is your way
of punishing me. I don't appreciate it!

184
00:24:21.379 --> 00:24:23.422
I don't know what you're talking about.

185
00:24:26.133 --> 00:24:30.137
I found these keys in my pocket.
so I assume I live here.

186
00:24:31.973 --> 00:24:34.475
- You supposed to be my wife?
- Supposed to be?

187
00:24:35.559 --> 00:24:36.852
John!

188
00:24:37.937 --> 00:24:42.108
You really... don't know who I am. do you?

189
00:24:43.067 --> 00:24:45.486
Your doctor called me.
He was worried that this might happen.

190
00:24:45.611 --> 00:24:47.488
My doctor?

191
00:24:47.613 --> 00:24:51.951
Yeah. He... he gave me his card.

192
00:24:52.076 --> 00:24:54.537
He's desperate to find you.

193
00:24:55.538 --> 00:24:58.332
Schreber...

194
00:25:01.460 --> 00:25:03.421
I feel like I'm living out
someone else's nightmare.

195
00:25:03.546 --> 00:25:06.298
What happened to me?
Why was I seeing a doctor?

196
00:25:07.049 --> 00:25:09.218
I had an affair.

197
00:25:10.302 --> 00:25:12.680
You were angry at me.

198
00:25:14.974 --> 00:25:16.976
The police are looking for you.

199
00:25:17.101 --> 00:25:19.020
I know. I saw the papers.

200
00:25:19.145 --> 00:25:22.023
"Killer Stalks City Streetwalkers."

201
00:25:25.484 --> 00:25:31.240
I was with one of those women.
before I came here tonight.

202
00:25:31.365 --> 00:25:34.702
- I don't understand.
- I met her outside an Automat.

203
00:25:35.703 --> 00:25:37.788
I guess I wanted to test myself.

204
00:25:39.415 --> 00:25:42.710
I wanted to know if I had it in me
to do those things.

205
00:25:42.835 --> 00:25:47.381
Maybe I have lost my mind. but whoever I am.
I'm still me and I'm not a killer.

206
00:25:53.387 --> 00:25:55.139
I believe you.

207
00:25:56.640 --> 00:25:58.059
You do?

208
00:26:01.937 --> 00:26:02.980
What?

209
00:26:03.105 --> 00:26:05.816
The car outside. the one you arrived in.

210
00:26:05.941 --> 00:26:08.360
It's a cop. He dropped me off here.

211
00:26:10.362 --> 00:26:12.948
I didn't know he was still here.

212
00:26:13.074 --> 00:26:14.492
John!

213
00:26:15.409 --> 00:26:18.037
Hold it right there. Mister!

214
00:26:19.205 --> 00:26:21.415
Wait. You have the wrong man.

215
00:26:21.540 --> 00:26:23.876
- Stand aside. will you. please?
- I didn't kill anyone.

216
00:26:24.001 --> 00:26:27.588
Right now. what you are is a suspect.
Turn yourself in.

217
00:26:27.713 --> 00:26:29.548
I'll listen to whatever you have to say.

218
00:26:29.673 --> 00:26:32.551
You're not gonna believe what I have to say.

219
00:26:32.676 --> 00:26:36.180
- Try me.
- There's someone after me.

220
00:26:36.305 --> 00:26:39.558
There's this group of men. they want me dead.

221
00:26:39.683 --> 00:26:42.728
And I don't even know if... they're not even...

222
00:26:42.853 --> 00:26:46.357
- Yeah. who's gonna listen to a madman?
- Stand aside. Mrs. Murdoch.

223
00:26:46.482 --> 00:26:47.983
Run!

224
00:26:51.904 --> 00:26:54.532
No one ever listens to me.

225
00:26:59.787 --> 00:27:01.205
Murdoch. stop!

226
00:27:06.127 --> 00:27:07.628
Murdoch!

227
00:27:43.956 --> 00:27:46.417
- How much further?
- We're almost there. buddy.

228
00:27:49.003 --> 00:27:52.089
Hey. you happen to know the way to Shell Beach?

229
00:27:52.214 --> 00:27:55.426
You're kidding. Me and the missus
spent our honeymoon there.

230
00:27:55.551 --> 00:27:58.179
All you gotta do is take Main Street West to...

231
00:28:00.723 --> 00:28:02.725
Or is it the cross...?

232
00:28:02.850 --> 00:28:04.852
You know. that's funny.

233
00:28:04.977 --> 00:28:08.731
I can't seem to remember
if it's Main Street West or the crosstown.

234
00:28:13.319 --> 00:28:16.572
I'm sorry. Inspector.
I cannot be of more assistance.

235
00:28:16.697 --> 00:28:18.532
but I am running late for an appointment.

236
00:28:18.657 --> 00:28:21.076
Well. I appreciate your taking the time.

237
00:28:29.418 --> 00:28:31.629
There's just one thing that puzzles me.

238
00:28:31.754 --> 00:28:36.383
I've met quite a few murderers
in the course of my work.

239
00:28:36.508 --> 00:28:39.094
Murdoch doesn't strike me as one.

240
00:28:39.220 --> 00:28:42.181
Perhaps you are not accustomed
to digging deep enough.

241
00:28:42.306 --> 00:28:45.351
Well. I do know when someone
is lying to me. Doctor.

242
00:28:45.476 --> 00:28:48.020
Forgive me. Inspector.
but you are not a clinician.

243
00:28:48.145 --> 00:28:51.815
Judging personalities happens to be my business.

244
00:28:51.941 --> 00:28:53.859
Well. maybe you could give me a few pointers.

245
00:28:53.984 --> 00:28:55.611
Certainly.

246
00:28:55.736 --> 00:28:57.821
Let's take you. for instance.

247
00:28:57.947 --> 00:29:03.160
You are a fastidious man.
driven. consumed by details.

248
00:29:04.119 --> 00:29:06.080
I would say your life is...

249
00:29:07.373 --> 00:29:08.958
rather lonely.

250
00:29:09.083 --> 00:29:11.627
Good evening. Inspector.
I really must be going.

251
00:29:53.085 --> 00:29:57.006
'Closing time. The pool is now closed.'

252
00:30:03.971 --> 00:30:05.139
Dr. Schreber.

253
00:30:06.682 --> 00:30:11.478
Most unfortunate it is that
we were forced to seek you out here.

254
00:30:12.396 --> 00:30:16.692
You know how uncomfortable
we find all this... moisture.

255
00:30:17.484 --> 00:30:20.738
- I'm sorry. I...
- Failed to report in. yes.

256
00:30:20.863 --> 00:30:23.407
I was frightened. I have a weak heart. you know.

257
00:30:23.532 --> 00:30:27.077
Your weakness is not. we think.
an affair of the heart.

258
00:30:27.202 --> 00:30:29.997
We found this in his hotel room.

259
00:30:30.122 --> 00:30:33.542
Must we reproduce Mr. Murdoch's memories again?

260
00:30:33.667 --> 00:30:35.085
I tried to imprint him.

261
00:30:35.210 --> 00:30:37.212
but he woke up. he knocked
the syringe right out of my hand.

262
00:30:37.338 --> 00:30:39.381
I tried to stop him. but he was too fast.

263
00:30:39.506 --> 00:30:42.134
- He has no memories. then?
- Only fragments.

264
00:30:42.259 --> 00:30:43.969
The procedure. it was interrupted.

265
00:30:44.094 --> 00:30:47.264
I guess it's only a matter of rounding him up.

266
00:30:47.389 --> 00:30:51.477
- You have had strays before. right?
- This is no stray. Doctor.

267
00:30:51.602 --> 00:30:53.103
This one can tune.

268
00:30:53.228 --> 00:30:56.065
But that's impossible.
I thought only you had that ability.

269
00:30:56.190 --> 00:31:00.652
You will process another template
of the subject's memories. yes?

270
00:31:00.778 --> 00:31:04.031
- Of course. I'll imprint him again.
- No.

271
00:31:04.156 --> 00:31:07.534
We require them for a quite different purpose.

272
00:31:07.659 --> 00:31:10.287
It's almost midnight. Dr. Schreber.

273
00:31:10.412 --> 00:31:15.125
We'll talk again after tonight's tuning.
but no more delays. yes?

274
00:31:15.250 --> 00:31:19.963
No more... inconsistencies in your behavior.

275
00:31:27.513 --> 00:31:29.515
You appear quite frail. Doctor.

276
00:31:30.933 --> 00:31:33.811
Perhaps some exercise would do you good.

277
00:31:48.283 --> 00:31:50.285
- Come in.
- Kate.

278
00:31:54.540 --> 00:31:56.625
- How is he?
- The same.

279
00:31:57.418 --> 00:32:00.129
Walenski? It's me. Frank.

280
00:32:06.510 --> 00:32:08.178
Come in. Frank.

281
00:32:10.806 --> 00:32:12.474
Close the door.

282
00:32:20.232 --> 00:32:23.360
I've been looking through
some of your old reports.

283
00:32:23.485 --> 00:32:25.571
It's an interesting case.

284
00:32:26.697 --> 00:32:29.950
The kind that can make a man's career.

285
00:32:31.702 --> 00:32:35.247
- Or break it.
- Yeah. I was on that case.

286
00:32:35.372 --> 00:32:39.126
And then. what? What happened then. Eddie?

287
00:32:39.251 --> 00:32:41.003
Nothing happened. Frank.

288
00:32:41.128 --> 00:32:45.591
I've just been spending time
on the subway. riding in circles.

289
00:32:45.716 --> 00:32:49.470
Thinking in circles. There's no way out.

290
00:32:51.346 --> 00:32:53.182
I've been over every inch of this city.

291
00:32:57.978 --> 00:32:59.980
You're scaring your wife to death. Eddie.

292
00:33:00.105 --> 00:33:01.982
She's not my wife.

293
00:33:03.317 --> 00:33:06.236
I don't know who she is.
I don't know who any of us are.

294
00:33:06.361 --> 00:33:08.322
What makes you say that?

295
00:33:08.447 --> 00:33:10.782
Do you think about the past much. Frank?

296
00:33:11.867 --> 00:33:14.244
As much as the next guy.

297
00:33:14.369 --> 00:33:16.955
See. I've been trying to remember things.

298
00:33:17.080 --> 00:33:20.000
clearly remember things from my past.

299
00:33:20.125 --> 00:33:25.380
But the more I try to think back.
the more it all starts to unravel.

300
00:33:25.506 --> 00:33:30.802
None of it seems real.
it's like I've just been dreaming this life.

301
00:33:30.928 --> 00:33:33.847
and when I finally wake up.
I'll be somebody else.

302
00:33:33.972 --> 00:33:35.682
Somebody totally different.

303
00:33:40.479 --> 00:33:43.565
You saw something. didn't you. Eddie?

304
00:33:43.690 --> 00:33:46.318
Something to do with the case.

305
00:33:46.443 --> 00:33:50.239
There is no case! There never was!

306
00:33:50.364 --> 00:33:54.701
It's all just a big joke! It's a joke!

307
00:34:35.659 --> 00:34:37.661
<i>Tonight's requirements are:</i>

308
00:34:37.786 --> 00:34:42.791
<i>twelve family photo albums. nine personal diaries.</i>

309
00:34:42.916 --> 00:34:47.671
<i>seventeen love letters. assorted childhood photographs.</i>

310
00:34:47.796 --> 00:34:51.800
<i>twenty-six wallets. ID's and social security cards...</i>

311
00:34:51.925 --> 00:34:54.011
These do bring back memories.

312
00:34:56.305 --> 00:34:58.599
This one is still warm.

313
00:34:59.308 --> 00:35:03.687
What is it? The recollections of a great lover?

314
00:35:03.812 --> 00:35:08.275
A catalog of conquests?
We will soon find out.

315
00:35:09.526 --> 00:35:14.281
You wouldn't appreciate that. would you.
Mr. whatever-your-name-is?

316
00:35:14.406 --> 00:35:18.702
Not the sort of conquests you would ever understand.

317
00:35:19.536 --> 00:35:20.704
Let's see.

318
00:35:22.080 --> 00:35:24.708
A touch of unhappy childhood.

319
00:35:30.422 --> 00:35:33.258
A dash of teenage rebellion.

320
00:35:34.885 --> 00:35:37.095
And last but not least...

321
00:35:37.846 --> 00:35:39.765
a tragic death in the family.

322
00:35:39.890 --> 00:35:41.141
Doctor.

323
00:35:43.143 --> 00:35:44.353
Mr. Book.

324
00:35:51.777 --> 00:35:55.489
Why does Murdoch not sleep
during the tuning as the others do?

325
00:35:55.614 --> 00:35:59.618
I don't know. Maybe he's a step
up the evolutionary ladder.

326
00:35:59.743 --> 00:36:02.454
A freak of nature. He's adapting to survive.

327
00:36:02.579 --> 00:36:05.916
What do you expect?
Weren't you looking for the human soul?

328
00:36:06.041 --> 00:36:08.543
That's the purpose of your little zoo. isn't it?

329
00:36:08.669 --> 00:36:11.922
That's why you keep changing people
and things around every night.

330
00:36:12.047 --> 00:36:14.675
Maybe you have finally found
what you are looking for.

331
00:36:14.800 --> 00:36:17.260
and it's going to bite you on your...

332
00:36:20.389 --> 00:36:23.975
It requires several of your lifetimes
to master our gifts.

333
00:36:24.101 --> 00:36:27.854
The idea that a simple man
could develop the ability to tune is...

334
00:36:27.979 --> 00:36:31.566
Absurd. I know.
But what other explanation is there?

335
00:36:36.405 --> 00:36:38.073
It is time.

336
00:37:23.368 --> 00:37:24.870
Shut it down.

337
00:37:36.798 --> 00:37:38.300
Hey. wake up!

338
00:37:38.425 --> 00:37:41.887
Get your paper right here!

339
00:37:53.315 --> 00:37:58.069
It's driving me crazy. I can't sleep.
And they call my job "unskilled".

340
00:37:58.195 --> 00:38:02.365
You think you've got it tough? You try
looking after these kids for a change!

341
00:38:02.491 --> 00:38:07.078
Anyways. Frederickson says he'll take me
off the damn night shift soon.

342
00:38:07.204 --> 00:38:09.164
Well. it's about time. dear.

343
00:39:24.781 --> 00:39:25.949
Hello?

344
00:39:28.660 --> 00:39:29.911
Hello?

345
00:39:34.207 --> 00:39:36.585
Wake up! Hey!

346
00:39:39.045 --> 00:39:41.673
Wake up! Wake up!

347
00:39:44.009 --> 00:39:45.844
Wake up!

348
00:39:47.178 --> 00:39:48.597
Hello?

349
00:39:50.265 --> 00:39:53.435
Can anyone hear me?

350
00:39:55.562 --> 00:39:58.565
Let the tuning commence.

351
00:42:38.224 --> 00:42:41.603
The Goodwins. Jeremy. Sylvia.

352
00:42:41.728 --> 00:42:43.897
Jane and little Matthew.

353
00:42:47.734 --> 00:42:49.819
Jane and little Matthew.

354
00:43:19.974 --> 00:43:22.227
The rich get richer.

355
00:43:22.352 --> 00:43:25.563
Probably have maid's quarters
before the night is through.

356
00:44:19.367 --> 00:44:21.286
Dr. Schreber. I presume.

357
00:44:21.953 --> 00:44:24.164
- It's you!
- Hey. come on.

358
00:44:24.289 --> 00:44:28.293
That's no way to greet a patient. Doctor.
If that's what you are... Doctor?

359
00:44:28.418 --> 00:44:29.794
Mr. Murdoch. please. I...

360
00:44:29.919 --> 00:44:31.629
What is happening here?
Why is everyone asleep?

361
00:44:31.754 --> 00:44:34.048
Please keep your voice down.

362
00:44:34.174 --> 00:44:36.009
Why can't I remember anything?
What have you done to me?

363
00:44:36.134 --> 00:44:38.803
Nothing. nothing. Please. I want to help you.

364
00:44:38.928 --> 00:44:42.390
We cannot talk here. It is not safe.
If they see us together. they'll...

365
00:44:42.515 --> 00:44:45.226
I don't care. I want some answers.
I want some answers now!

366
00:44:45.351 --> 00:44:48.396
Who are they? Why are they trying to kill me?

367
00:44:48.521 --> 00:44:49.606
Answer me!

368
00:44:54.777 --> 00:44:59.324
- My god. you really can do it.
- I did that?

369
00:44:59.449 --> 00:45:03.453
Listen to me. John. You have their power.
You can make things happen by will alone.

370
00:45:03.578 --> 00:45:07.081
They call it "tuning". That is how
they make the buildings change.

371
00:45:07.207 --> 00:45:09.667
Just now. you acted out of self-defense. a reflex.

372
00:45:09.792 --> 00:45:12.462
But I can teach you to control
your power consciously.

373
00:45:12.587 --> 00:45:14.797
Let me help you. John.
Together we can stop them.

374
00:45:14.923 --> 00:45:17.926
We can take the city back.

375
00:45:19.844 --> 00:45:21.846
My glasses.

376
00:45:22.972 --> 00:45:25.016
My glasses. please!

377
00:46:12.021 --> 00:46:14.440
He made a terrible impression for the firm.

378
00:46:14.565 --> 00:46:17.151
lollygagging around as he did.

379
00:46:17.277 --> 00:46:20.071
So. I simply told Frederickson
I was going to have to let him go.

380
00:46:20.196 --> 00:46:22.824
And well you should have. darling.

381
00:46:22.949 --> 00:46:24.534
He attacked me.

382
00:46:25.368 --> 00:46:28.997
- I don't know where he has gone.
- Come. Dr. Schreber.

383
00:46:30.373 --> 00:46:33.251
We have much to do. yes?

384
00:46:34.585 --> 00:46:35.878
Yes.

385
00:48:26.864 --> 00:48:30.535
Tonight's experiment shall be conducted
in the following locations.

386
00:48:30.660 --> 00:48:34.497
The first subject shall be imprinted
here on Avenue M.

387
00:48:34.622 --> 00:48:37.583
Mr. Book. there is a... problem.

388
00:48:37.708 --> 00:48:40.962
There is no Avenue M.
We were unable to complete it.

389
00:48:41.087 --> 00:48:44.507
During the last tuning.
we detected a lack of control.

390
00:48:44.632 --> 00:48:47.427
An opposing influence on the machines?

391
00:48:47.552 --> 00:48:51.848
Then. this man Murdoch is
more powerful than we thought.

392
00:48:51.973 --> 00:48:54.016
He's becoming like us.

393
00:48:54.142 --> 00:48:57.603
So we must become like him.

394
00:48:58.438 --> 00:49:00.690
The good doctor has done as we asked?

395
00:49:00.815 --> 00:49:04.444
The life and times of John Murdoch. Volume 2.

396
00:49:06.612 --> 00:49:09.073
We must not do this.

397
00:49:09.198 --> 00:49:12.660
Murdoch does not possess these memories. yes?

398
00:49:12.785 --> 00:49:15.371
How will his imprint allow us to find him?

399
00:49:15.496 --> 00:49:19.917
Everywhere he goes. everyone
he seeks out. will be known to us.

400
00:49:20.042 --> 00:49:25.465
And as he follows the clues.
so shall we follow the memories.

401
00:49:25.590 --> 00:49:28.134
Perhaps we have forgotten
what happened last time. when we...

402
00:49:28.259 --> 00:49:31.304
Yes. Poor. poor Mr...

403
00:49:31.429 --> 00:49:33.222
We have not forgotten.

404
00:49:33.347 --> 00:49:40.521
If Mr. Hand wishes to make this sacrifice
for the greater good.

405
00:49:40.646 --> 00:49:42.398
so be it.

406
00:49:42.523 --> 00:49:47.820
But to imprint one of us...
Failure has always resulted.

407
00:49:47.945 --> 00:49:51.407
What Mr. Hand proposes is our only option.

408
00:49:51.532 --> 00:49:53.034
Imprint.

409
00:49:58.289 --> 00:50:00.291
This may sting a bit.

410
00:50:36.994 --> 00:50:38.996
Is it done?

411
00:50:39.622 --> 00:50:41.541
Oh. yes. Mr. Book.

412
00:50:43.042 --> 00:50:46.754
I have John Murdoch in mind.

413
00:50:51.425 --> 00:50:56.639
<i>Johnny. I found this postcard among your mother's things.</i>

414
00:50:56.764 --> 00:51:00.768
<i>Brings back memories. doesn't it? Stop by sometime.</i>

415
00:51:00.893 --> 00:51:04.146
<i>We'll see if we can't hook ourselves another mermaid.</i>

416
00:51:04.272 --> 00:51:06.274
<i>Love to Emma. Karl.</i>

417
00:51:11.654 --> 00:51:12.655
Karl.

418
00:51:14.949 --> 00:51:16.659
Karl Harris.

419
00:51:24.834 --> 00:51:27.461
Harris... Harris...

420
00:51:30.339 --> 00:51:32.133
Harris. Karl.

421
00:51:34.135 --> 00:51:36.470
Excuse me. can you tell me the way to Avenue C?

422
00:51:37.138 --> 00:51:38.472
Try the subway.

423
00:51:42.768 --> 00:51:47.023
- You got a problem. pal?
- You... been working here long?

424
00:51:47.982 --> 00:51:51.319
Twenty-five years. No days off for good behavior.

425
00:52:16.636 --> 00:52:20.890
We're looking for John Murdoch.

426
00:52:53.756 --> 00:52:55.758
She knows nothing. Mr. Hand.

427
00:52:55.883 --> 00:52:57.551
A dead end. yes. Mr. Wall?

428
00:52:57.677 --> 00:53:00.388
We thought his imprint would allow us
to track him. yes?

429
00:53:00.513 --> 00:53:03.015
But instead. we have been brought here.

430
00:53:03.140 --> 00:53:07.061
- This is irrational.
- Instincts are irrational. Mr. Wall.

431
00:53:07.186 --> 00:53:10.398
And we must follow where they lead. yes?

432
00:53:10.523 --> 00:53:15.069
Mr. Sleep suggests he may go
to places familiar... his job.

433
00:53:15.194 --> 00:53:17.154
He does not care about our job.

434
00:53:17.279 --> 00:53:19.907
Indulge us. Mr. Hand.

435
00:53:20.032 --> 00:53:22.702
If you were Murdoch. yes?

436
00:53:22.827 --> 00:53:26.288
If... I were Murdoch...

437
00:53:27.957 --> 00:53:34.463
I would remember how my wife had
hurt me by sleeping with another man.

438
00:53:35.464 --> 00:53:41.595
And then... I would look for a way
to hurt her in return.

439
00:53:44.932 --> 00:53:47.768
Leave me alone with her.

440
00:53:47.893 --> 00:53:49.603
There's work to be done.

441
00:53:53.065 --> 00:53:55.401
<i>All change. platform three.</i>

442
00:53:55.526 --> 00:53:59.363
- <i>Platform three. all change.
- All change?</i>

443
00:53:59.488 --> 00:54:01.365
Excuse me. How do I get to the end of the line?

444
00:54:01.490 --> 00:54:02.950
You want the Express.

445
00:54:10.624 --> 00:54:13.961
<i>...train leaving on platform seven.</i>

446
00:54:14.086 --> 00:54:15.421
- Platform two.
- Thanks a lot.

447
00:54:15.546 --> 00:54:19.467
- Hey! How come that train didn't stop?
- That's the Express.

448
00:54:20.843 --> 00:54:22.720
There's no way out. you know?

449
00:54:22.845 --> 00:54:26.515
You can't get out of the city.
Believe me. I've tried.

450
00:54:26.640 --> 00:54:30.478
You're Murdoch. aren't you?
The one they've been looking for.

451
00:54:30.603 --> 00:54:33.063
- Who are you?
- Used to be a cop.

452
00:54:33.189 --> 00:54:35.691
At least. in this life. I was.

453
00:54:35.816 --> 00:54:38.194
They steal people's memories. you know?

454
00:54:38.319 --> 00:54:40.321
Then. they swap them around between us.

455
00:54:40.446 --> 00:54:42.948
I've seen them do it.
back and forth. back and forth.

456
00:54:43.073 --> 00:54:45.159
till no one knows who they are anymore.

457
00:54:45.284 --> 00:54:46.660
How do you know all this?

458
00:54:46.786 --> 00:54:50.831
Once in a while. one of us wakes up
while they're changing things.

459
00:54:50.956 --> 00:54:53.375
It's not supposed to happen. but it does.

460
00:54:53.501 --> 00:54:55.419
It happened to me.

461
00:54:55.544 --> 00:54:58.464
They'll come looking for you. Murdoch.

462
00:54:58.589 --> 00:55:00.841
Just like they'll come looking for me!

463
00:55:00.966 --> 00:55:03.761
But that's okay. I figured a way out!

464
00:55:15.231 --> 00:55:17.399
They were here.

465
00:55:18.484 --> 00:55:21.987
- Last night.
- This was to be his home.

466
00:55:23.447 --> 00:55:26.617
That was when we loved her.

467
00:55:26.742 --> 00:55:28.994
This is all well and good. Mr. Hand.

468
00:55:29.119 --> 00:55:33.082
but we require a more practical link
to his present whereabouts.

469
00:55:35.793 --> 00:55:36.961
Yes.

470
00:55:37.837 --> 00:55:40.506
And I know where to find her.

471
00:55:48.430 --> 00:55:52.393
- We're very lucky. when you think about it.
- I'm sorry?

472
00:55:52.518 --> 00:55:57.356
To be able to revisit those places
which have meant so very much to us.

473
00:55:57.481 --> 00:55:59.608
I thought it was more that we were haunted by them.

474
00:55:59.733 --> 00:56:01.151
Perhaps.

475
00:56:03.195 --> 00:56:06.949
But imagine a life alien to yours.

476
00:56:07.783 --> 00:56:09.660
in which your memories were not your own

477
00:56:09.785 --> 00:56:12.621
but those shared by every other of your kind.

478
00:56:13.998 --> 00:56:17.001
Imagine the torment of such an existence.

479
00:56:18.377 --> 00:56:21.297
No experiences to call your own.

480
00:56:23.299 --> 00:56:27.553
If it was all you knew.
maybe it would be a comfort.

481
00:56:28.262 --> 00:56:30.890
But if you were to discover something different...

482
00:56:32.141 --> 00:56:34.518
something better.

483
00:56:38.689 --> 00:56:41.108
There used to be a ferry when I was a boy.

484
00:56:41.233 --> 00:56:46.322
Biggest thing you ever saw.
lit up like a floating birthday cake.

485
00:56:47.448 --> 00:56:51.619
That's just what my husband
once said to me. on this very spot.

486
00:56:52.995 --> 00:56:54.830
Where is your husband now?

487
00:56:54.955 --> 00:56:58.334
I wish I knew. What brings you here?

488
00:56:59.168 --> 00:57:02.087
I met my wife at this place.

489
00:57:02.212 --> 00:57:06.133
- It's where I first met my husband.
- Small world.

490
00:57:26.904 --> 00:57:30.324
No. no. no!

491
00:57:59.186 --> 00:58:00.938
Hello?

492
00:58:02.147 --> 00:58:03.565
Hello?

493
00:58:48.652 --> 00:58:52.031
- What are you doing here?
- I've been following you.

494
00:58:55.868 --> 00:58:57.578
Hold it right there!

495
00:58:59.621 --> 00:59:02.750
Johnny? Johnny!

496
00:59:03.792 --> 00:59:07.504
It's been so damn long.
I thought you'd forgotten your Uncle Karl.

497
00:59:08.338 --> 00:59:10.758
You son of a gun!

498
00:59:13.177 --> 00:59:14.595
Uncle Karl...

499
00:59:18.140 --> 00:59:19.475
Wait.

500
00:59:21.852 --> 00:59:24.104
- Is that me?
- Yeah.

501
00:59:33.155 --> 00:59:35.199
Shell Beach is where I grew up?

502
00:59:35.324 --> 00:59:38.786
That's what I said. Shell Beach. your hometown.

503
00:59:38.911 --> 00:59:41.371
I need to get there. Karl. How do I get there?

504
00:59:42.539 --> 00:59:45.250
I don't know. I haven't been there in years.

505
00:59:45.375 --> 00:59:48.837
Come on. you must remember.
You gotta have some idea.

506
00:59:48.962 --> 00:59:51.590
- Come on!
- Sorry. Johnny.

507
00:59:53.217 --> 00:59:56.095
The old cracker barrel ain't what it used to be.

508
00:59:59.515 --> 01:00:03.560
- So bright there.
- Brighter times. I guess.

509
01:00:05.312 --> 01:00:07.648
You were always scribbling in that damn book.

510
01:00:08.398 --> 01:00:12.861
That's me and your pa.
What a couple of handsome fools!

511
01:00:14.196 --> 01:00:16.782
What happened to my parents?

512
01:00:20.369 --> 01:00:22.412
Where are they now?

513
01:00:22.538 --> 01:00:26.959
They're dead. Johnny.
They died when their house burnt down.

514
01:00:27.084 --> 01:00:31.588
I looked after you.
You don't remember that. really?

515
01:00:34.758 --> 01:00:36.176
What's that?

516
01:00:36.301 --> 01:00:38.554
What is that?

517
01:00:43.433 --> 01:00:45.102
It's a scar.

518
01:00:45.227 --> 01:00:47.688
You burnt your arm pretty bad in the fire.

519
01:00:53.318 --> 01:00:56.530
- What does it mean. Johnny?
- It means these are all lies!

520
01:01:00.200 --> 01:01:02.411
Why are you here. Mrs. Murdoch?

521
01:01:11.461 --> 01:01:14.047
My husband told me he'd been here.

522
01:01:17.718 --> 01:01:21.305
He told me he wanted to test himself.

523
01:01:21.430 --> 01:01:25.767
see if he was capable of...

524
01:01:34.902 --> 01:01:38.739
I wanted to talk to her. I thought
maybe she could help me find him.

525
01:01:40.490 --> 01:01:42.910
Stay here. I'm gonna call the station.

526
01:01:53.587 --> 01:01:58.884
Yeah. this is Bumstead. Send the homicide
coroner to 1440 East. yeah.

527
01:01:59.009 --> 01:02:00.761
There's been another one.

528
01:02:01.803 --> 01:02:04.640
It's the same pattern.
I'll explain when you get here.

529
01:02:15.317 --> 01:02:17.194
Oh. god.

530
01:02:17.319 --> 01:02:20.364
It's okay. I won't hurt you. It's okay.

531
01:02:31.500 --> 01:02:35.545
- Where the hell did she come from?
- I found her hiding.

532
01:02:35.671 --> 01:02:37.547
She saw what happened here.

533
01:03:04.700 --> 01:03:07.661
Are you ready to go home. Mrs. Murdoch?

534
01:03:07.786 --> 01:03:10.539
The Inspector is gonna take me. Thanks.

535
01:03:35.147 --> 01:03:36.565
It's beautiful.

536
01:03:39.151 --> 01:03:43.613
It was a gift from my mother. She died recently.

537
01:03:44.948 --> 01:03:47.367
I keep it with me to remind me of her.

538
01:03:49.328 --> 01:03:50.662
I'm sorry.

539
01:03:54.082 --> 01:03:56.168
It's a funny thing. though.

540
01:03:56.293 --> 01:03:58.670
I can't remember when she gave it to me.

541
01:04:01.214 --> 01:04:04.217
How do you think I could forget a thing like that?

542
01:04:06.219 --> 01:04:10.557
Do you think about the past much. Mrs. Murdoch?

543
01:04:12.726 --> 01:04:14.561
What's happening. Inspector?

544
01:04:15.854 --> 01:04:18.231
I'm not sure I know anymore.

545
01:04:21.693 --> 01:04:24.321
I left your old room like it was.

546
01:04:24.446 --> 01:04:26.490
You can sleep here tonight...

547
01:04:26.615 --> 01:04:30.786
Glad to have you back. Johnny.
even if it is for just a night.

548
01:04:30.911 --> 01:04:32.704
Karl.

549
01:04:32.829 --> 01:04:35.415
- Is that the right time?
- Why. sure.

550
01:04:35.540 --> 01:04:37.918
That clock's kept perfect time since I bought it.

551
01:04:38.043 --> 01:04:42.339
- Am or pm?
- What do you think. Johnny?

552
01:04:42.464 --> 01:04:44.341
I don't understand.
How can it be night already?

553
01:04:44.466 --> 01:04:48.845
- What happened to the day? How'd I miss it?
- You're tired. Anything's possible.

554
01:04:48.970 --> 01:04:54.393
Look... get some sleep.
We'll straighten all this out tomorrow.

555
01:05:20.252 --> 01:05:23.004
"Guide to Shell Beach" by Johnny Murdoch.

556
01:05:25.549 --> 01:05:26.800
Oh. come on.

557
01:05:46.194 --> 01:05:48.613
- Hello?
- Emma. he's here.

558
01:05:48.738 --> 01:05:52.868
- <i>He's acting mighty peculiar.
- I know. He's not himself.</i>

559
01:05:52.993 --> 01:05:55.203
Keep him there. and I'll be right over.

560
01:05:55.328 --> 01:05:57.456
- I'll try.
- Thanks. Karl. Bye.

561
01:05:59.833 --> 01:06:00.834
Johnny!

562
01:06:00.959 --> 01:06:04.337
I can't promise anything. Mrs. Murdoch.
We just have to play it as it comes.

563
01:06:04.463 --> 01:06:07.924
Johnny. we... We just wanted to help!

564
01:06:14.681 --> 01:06:18.101
Karl... Uncle Karl.

565
01:06:18.226 --> 01:06:22.230
Johnny. if you're in some kind of trouble.
maybe we could do something.

566
01:06:23.190 --> 01:06:27.694
Haven't seen you in so long. yes.

567
01:07:40.392 --> 01:07:45.730
Mr. Murdoch. you've been the cause
of much distress.

568
01:07:49.734 --> 01:07:52.237
- Start talking.
- There's no need for this.

569
01:07:52.362 --> 01:07:55.699
There's no escape. The city's ours. We made it.

570
01:07:55.824 --> 01:07:57.284
What are you talking about?

571
01:07:57.409 --> 01:08:00.287
We fashioned this city on stolen memories.

572
01:08:00.412 --> 01:08:04.165
different eras. different pasts. all rolled into one.

573
01:08:04.291 --> 01:08:08.420
Each night. we revise it. refine it. in order to learn.

574
01:08:08.545 --> 01:08:11.339
- Learn what?
- About you. Mr. Murdoch.

575
01:08:11.464 --> 01:08:15.969
You and your fellow inhabitants. what makes you human.

576
01:08:16.094 --> 01:08:19.431
- Why?
- We need to be like you.

577
01:08:20.140 --> 01:08:22.225
I understand you now. Mr. Murdoch.

578
01:08:22.350 --> 01:08:25.979
I remember that which you do not.
what you've been missing.

579
01:08:26.104 --> 01:08:31.318
The ocean. yes. running along the waves as a child.

580
01:08:31.443 --> 01:08:36.906
meeting Emma at the river.
that first kiss that followed.

581
01:08:37.032 --> 01:08:39.909
- What are you?
- You've seen what we are.

582
01:08:40.035 --> 01:08:42.871
We use your dead as vessels.

583
01:10:52.584 --> 01:10:54.127
Get in!

584
01:11:09.017 --> 01:11:12.896
- What about her? Ring any bells?
- She was alive when I left her.

585
01:11:13.021 --> 01:11:15.857
- What about this?
- This is nothing. This is...

586
01:11:15.982 --> 01:11:18.443
It must mean something. all those pictures.

587
01:11:18.568 --> 01:11:21.654
What pictures? I don't understand this.

588
01:11:21.780 --> 01:11:24.532
Stop playing games with me. Murdoch!
Stop telling me lies!

589
01:11:24.657 --> 01:11:28.328
- I am not telling you lies!
- Help me out here. Make me understand.

590
01:11:28.453 --> 01:11:30.455
I have this jigsaw puzzle in front of my face.

591
01:11:30.580 --> 01:11:33.875
and every time I try to rearrange
the pieces. it still doesn't make any sense.

592
01:11:34.000 --> 01:11:37.253
You think it makes sense to me?
I'm as much in the dark here as you are.

593
01:11:37.378 --> 01:11:39.422
You let me ask you a question?

594
01:11:40.548 --> 01:11:42.717
- You heard of a place called Shell Beach?
- Sure.

595
01:11:42.842 --> 01:11:44.719
- You know how to get there?
- Yeah.

596
01:11:44.844 --> 01:11:47.055
- You tell me?
- Ah. alright.

597
01:11:47.180 --> 01:11:50.016
You just... You go to the...

598
01:11:51.017 --> 01:11:54.187
- Where? Where do you go?
- Just give me a second. will you?

599
01:11:56.105 --> 01:11:58.024
You can't remember. can you?

600
01:12:00.401 --> 01:12:02.862
You think that's kind of odd?

601
01:12:04.030 --> 01:12:06.241
Wait. I got a better one for you.

602
01:12:06.366 --> 01:12:10.495
When was the last time you remember
doing something during the day?

603
01:12:10.620 --> 01:12:13.873
- What do you mean?
- I just mean. during the day.

604
01:12:14.833 --> 01:12:17.585
Daylight. When was the last time
you remember seeing it?

605
01:12:17.710 --> 01:12:21.297
And I'm not talking about some distant.
half-forgotten childhood memory.

606
01:12:21.422 --> 01:12:24.551
I mean. like. yesterday? Last week? When?

607
01:12:24.676 --> 01:12:26.970
Can you come up with a single memory?

608
01:12:28.304 --> 01:12:29.806
You can't. can you?

609
01:12:29.931 --> 01:12:35.854
You know something. I don't think
the sun even exists in this place.

610
01:12:35.979 --> 01:12:38.565
Cos I've been up for hours and hours and hours.

611
01:12:38.690 --> 01:12:40.900
and the night never ends here.

612
01:12:41.025 --> 01:12:43.194
- That is crazy.
- You're damn right this is crazy.

613
01:12:43.319 --> 01:12:45.905
But listen to me. Bumstead. It's not just me.

614
01:12:46.030 --> 01:12:49.576
It's all of us. They're doing something to all of us.

615
01:12:49.701 --> 01:12:52.412
- Shut up. you... I've heard enough.
- Please listen.

616
01:12:52.537 --> 01:12:54.163
Shut up. will you? Shut up!

617
01:13:04.507 --> 01:13:08.136
There has to be an explanation for this somewhere.

618
01:13:15.727 --> 01:13:17.312
Explain this.

619
01:13:37.790 --> 01:13:40.001
John. I'm so sorry.

620
01:13:41.127 --> 01:13:43.963
I never meant to hurt you. John.
And I did it. and I don't know why I did.

621
01:13:44.088 --> 01:13:48.760
- I wish I could take it all back.
- No. no. Emma. you didn't do it.

622
01:13:48.885 --> 01:13:52.847
This affair of yours. whatever it is.
the thing you're supposed to have done.

623
01:13:52.972 --> 01:13:54.933
you didn't do it. I don't believe it ever happened.

624
01:13:55.058 --> 01:13:58.686
- What do you mean?
- I know this is gonna sound crazy...

625
01:13:58.811 --> 01:14:01.898
But what if we never knew each other before now?

626
01:14:02.023 --> 01:14:05.026
What if the first time we ever met

627
01:14:05.151 --> 01:14:08.237
was last night in your... in our apartment.

628
01:14:08.363 --> 01:14:10.949
and everything you remember.

629
01:14:11.074 --> 01:14:14.077
and everything that I'm supposed
to remember. never really happened?

630
01:14:14.202 --> 01:14:16.704
Someone just wants us to think it did.

631
01:14:21.834 --> 01:14:23.878
You know. back in the apartment...

632
01:14:24.963 --> 01:14:27.715
I suddenly felt like I didn't know you at all.

633
01:14:29.258 --> 01:14:31.761
It was as if you were a stranger.

634
01:14:34.013 --> 01:14:39.060
But how can that be true?
I so vividly remember meeting you.

635
01:14:40.395 --> 01:14:42.939
I remember falling in love with you.

636
01:14:44.399 --> 01:14:46.526
I remember losing you.

637
01:14:46.651 --> 01:14:48.069
Time's up.

638
01:14:48.987 --> 01:14:51.823
No. wait. wait. Please. just...

639
01:14:52.657 --> 01:14:54.659
Just one more minute?

640
01:15:00.206 --> 01:15:02.417
I love you. John.

641
01:15:05.169 --> 01:15:07.463
You can't fake something like that.

642
01:15:08.881 --> 01:15:10.717
No. you can't.

643
01:15:38.327 --> 01:15:41.956
Inspector? Sir?

644
01:15:43.624 --> 01:15:46.335
Detective Walenski killed himself last night.

645
01:15:46.461 --> 01:15:50.131
I... kind of thought you should know.

646
01:15:52.800 --> 01:15:55.428
Oh. and the chief wanted to see you.

647
01:15:56.637 --> 01:15:57.972
Sir?

648
01:16:03.936 --> 01:16:05.855
I knew you'd track the killer down. sir.

649
01:16:17.241 --> 01:16:19.202
Sir...

650
01:16:21.329 --> 01:16:22.538
Shoelace.

651
01:16:35.718 --> 01:16:38.888
- How can we help you. sir?
- You can sleep.

652
01:16:41.724 --> 01:16:44.060
- Gentlemen...
- Sleep. Sleep.

653
01:16:47.730 --> 01:16:49.148
Evening. sir.

654
01:16:57.740 --> 01:16:58.950
Bumstead.

655
01:17:01.828 --> 01:17:05.832
I wanted to be the first
to congratulate you about the case.

656
01:17:08.084 --> 01:17:10.878
Take us to Murdoch.

657
01:17:11.003 --> 01:17:12.421
Sleep.

658
01:17:39.699 --> 01:17:43.953
- Dr. Schreber.
- I knew you'd come eventually.

659
01:17:44.078 --> 01:17:46.539
Don't you think it's about time
you started giving me some answers?

660
01:17:46.664 --> 01:17:48.916
Yes. Yes. of course.

661
01:17:49.041 --> 01:17:51.085
Won't you please sit down?

662
01:17:53.921 --> 01:17:55.840
I come here quite often.

663
01:17:55.965 --> 01:17:58.342
It's one of the few places
I'm allowed a moment's peace.

664
01:17:58.467 --> 01:18:01.804
You see. they have an aversion to water.

665
01:18:02.889 --> 01:18:05.224
One could almost call it a phobia.

666
01:18:05.349 --> 01:18:08.686
Who are they? What do they want from me?

667
01:18:08.811 --> 01:18:10.271
Right.

668
01:18:10.396 --> 01:18:12.398
Well. for now. let's just say

669
01:18:12.523 --> 01:18:15.067
that you were the subject of their experiment.

670
01:18:15.193 --> 01:18:17.111
We all are.

671
01:18:18.571 --> 01:18:22.867
You're not crazy. John. And you're not a murderer.

672
01:18:25.286 --> 01:18:28.497
I'm sorry about this. I truly am.
but we do not have much time.

673
01:18:28.623 --> 01:18:31.292
and I cannot afford the luxury
of doing this the right way.

674
01:18:31.417 --> 01:18:35.087
Everything you need to know.
all the answers are in this syringe.

675
01:18:35.213 --> 01:18:38.799
I need you to inject yourself.
It's the only way to make you understand.

676
01:18:38.925 --> 01:18:41.385
- You're kidding me. right?
- We're running out of time. John.

677
01:18:41.510 --> 01:18:45.223
- You have to do this now.
- Give me the gun. Doctor.

678
01:18:45.348 --> 01:18:47.683
Inspector. he is more disturbed than we thought.

679
01:18:47.808 --> 01:18:50.436
I may not be the judge of personality
that you are. Doctor.

680
01:18:50.561 --> 01:18:54.065
but you're the one who looks disturbed to me.

681
01:18:54.190 --> 01:18:56.359
You do not know what you are doing.

682
01:18:57.401 --> 01:19:01.155
What exactly is in this. Doctor?

683
01:19:02.740 --> 01:19:06.035
All the answers you've been looking for.
John. I swear to you.

684
01:19:06.160 --> 01:19:11.666
Oh... Guess I'll just have
to hold on to it for safekeeping.

685
01:19:12.625 --> 01:19:15.670
- If you don't mind.
- Let's go. Doctor.

686
01:19:16.545 --> 01:19:19.924
Go? Where are we going?

687
01:19:20.049 --> 01:19:21.968
Shell Beach.

688
01:19:23.052 --> 01:19:25.388
That's where you want to go. isn't it?

689
01:19:25.513 --> 01:19:27.014
The ocean.

690
01:19:35.982 --> 01:19:40.903
Why are you doing this?
What do you hope to gain by helping me?

691
01:19:41.028 --> 01:19:42.488
The truth.

692
01:19:43.155 --> 01:19:46.242
None of these maps extend
far enough to show the ocean.

693
01:19:46.367 --> 01:19:49.620
You won't find anything there.
I promise you! I've been there and...

694
01:19:49.745 --> 01:19:52.915
If you've been there. you can show us
the way. then. can't you?

695
01:19:53.040 --> 01:19:54.917
We'll see for ourselves.

696
01:19:56.168 --> 01:20:00.631
I won't. I refuse. You can't make me go there!

697
01:20:13.477 --> 01:20:15.604
You were saying. Doctor?

698
01:20:27.283 --> 01:20:30.619
I don't understand. Used to be a bridge here.

699
01:20:37.418 --> 01:20:40.338
Try that again. your friends are gonna
be fishing you out of the canal!

700
01:20:40.463 --> 01:20:43.841
Don't hurt me. I'll tell you everything.
It doesn't matter anymore anyway.

701
01:20:50.681 --> 01:20:52.433
What?

702
01:20:55.019 --> 01:20:56.979
Who are you people?

703
01:21:01.150 --> 01:21:05.654
We will give you some more pretty things soon... Anna.

704
01:21:05.780 --> 01:21:07.531
I'm not Anna.

705
01:21:09.200 --> 01:21:11.369
You will be soon. yes.

706
01:21:15.206 --> 01:21:18.042
I have another use for her first.

707
01:21:24.590 --> 01:21:26.926
First. there was darkness.

708
01:21:28.094 --> 01:21:29.970
Then came the Strangers.

709
01:21:32.139 --> 01:21:34.683
They abducted us and brought us here.

710
01:21:35.726 --> 01:21:39.855
This city. everyone in it. is their experiment.

711
01:21:39.980 --> 01:21:42.650
They mix and match our memories as they see fit.

712
01:21:42.775 --> 01:21:46.070
trying to divine what makes us unique.

713
01:21:46.195 --> 01:21:48.823
One day. a man might be an inspector.

714
01:21:48.948 --> 01:21:52.034
The next. someone entirely different.

715
01:21:52.159 --> 01:21:55.371
When they want to study a murderer. for instance.

716
01:21:55.496 --> 01:22:00.292
they simply imprint one of their citizens
with a new personality.

717
01:22:00.418 --> 01:22:06.215
arrange a family for him. friends.
an entire history. even a lost wallet.

718
01:22:07.007 --> 01:22:09.385
Then they observe the results.

719
01:22:09.510 --> 01:22:14.014
Will a man. given the history
of a killer. continue in that vein?

720
01:22:14.140 --> 01:22:17.852
Or are we. in fact. more than
the mere sum of our memories?

721
01:22:17.977 --> 01:22:23.065
This business of you being a killer
was an unhappy coincidence.

722
01:22:23.190 --> 01:22:25.818
You have had dozens of lives before now.

723
01:22:25.943 --> 01:22:30.114
You just happened to wake up
while I was imprinting you with this one.

724
01:22:30.239 --> 01:22:32.283
Why are they doing all of this?

725
01:22:32.408 --> 01:22:35.327
It is our capacity for individuality.

726
01:22:35.453 --> 01:22:38.164
our souls that makes us different from them.

727
01:22:38.289 --> 01:22:40.458
They think they can find the human soul.

728
01:22:40.583 --> 01:22:43.878
if they understand how our memories work.

729
01:22:44.003 --> 01:22:47.923
All they have are collective memories.
They share one group mind.

730
01:22:48.048 --> 01:22:52.845
They're dying. you see? Their entire race
is on the brink of extinction.

731
01:22:52.970 --> 01:22:54.889
They think we can save them.

732
01:22:55.014 --> 01:22:58.017
- Where do I fit in?
- You are different. John.

733
01:22:58.142 --> 01:23:00.853
You resisted my attempt to imprint you.

734
01:23:05.399 --> 01:23:08.486
Somehow you have developed their ability to tune.

735
01:23:08.611 --> 01:23:11.780
That is how they change things.
That is how they built this city.

736
01:23:11.906 --> 01:23:15.075
They have machines buried deep beneath the surface.

737
01:23:15.201 --> 01:23:18.704
that allow them to focus their telepathic energies.

738
01:23:19.622 --> 01:23:22.041
<i>They control everything here. even the sun.</i>

739
01:23:22.166 --> 01:23:25.169
That's why it's always dark. they can't stand the light.

740
01:23:25.294 --> 01:23:26.795
So. why do they need you?

741
01:23:26.921 --> 01:23:30.758
<i>When they first brought us here. they extracted what was in us.'</i>

742
01:23:30.883 --> 01:23:35.054
So they could store the information. remix it like so much paint.

743
01:23:35.179 --> 01:23:37.640
and give us back new memories of their choosing.

744
01:23:37.765 --> 01:23:41.310
But they still needed an artist to help them.

745
01:23:43.145 --> 01:23:46.106
I understood the intricacies of the human mind

746
01:23:46.232 --> 01:23:48.526
better than they ever could.

747
01:23:48.651 --> 01:23:53.113
So. they allowed me to keep my skills
as a scientist. because they needed them.

748
01:23:53.239 --> 01:23:55.616
But they made me delete everything else.

749
01:24:04.124 --> 01:24:08.587
Can you imagine what it is like
being forced to erase your own past?

750
01:24:08.712 --> 01:24:12.800
What about my past? What about my childhood?

751
01:24:12.925 --> 01:24:17.096
Shell Beach. Uncle Karl... What about this?

752
01:24:18.597 --> 01:24:22.268
- This was blank when I found it!
- You still don't understand. John.

753
01:24:22.393 --> 01:24:25.479
You were never a boy. not in this place.

754
01:24:25.604 --> 01:24:30.234
Your entire history is an illusion.
a fabrication. as it is with all of us.

755
01:24:30.359 --> 01:24:33.028
You made those drawings happen with your gift.

756
01:24:33.153 --> 01:24:35.489
You say they brought us here.

757
01:24:36.699 --> 01:24:38.826
From where?

758
01:24:41.579 --> 01:24:44.748
I'm sorry. I don't remember.

759
01:24:45.749 --> 01:24:48.043
None of us remember that.

760
01:24:48.168 --> 01:24:52.172
what we once were. what we might have been.

761
01:24:52.298 --> 01:24:54.133
somewhere else.

762
01:25:11.150 --> 01:25:15.195
I've taken you this far. You don't need me anymore.

763
01:25:15.321 --> 01:25:16.947
Let's go.

764
01:25:35.174 --> 01:25:37.176
John...

765
01:26:01.283 --> 01:26:03.952
There is no ocean. John.

766
01:26:04.912 --> 01:26:07.206
There is nothing beyond the city.

767
01:26:08.707 --> 01:26:11.168
The only place home exists...

768
01:26:13.337 --> 01:26:15.339
is in your head.

769
01:26:23.681 --> 01:26:26.975
No! No! John. stop!

770
01:26:29.895 --> 01:26:30.979
No!

771
01:26:33.774 --> 01:26:35.109
Stop!

772
01:26:40.698 --> 01:26:43.409
Please! No!

773
01:27:02.428 --> 01:27:04.555
And now you know the truth.

774
01:27:23.991 --> 01:27:25.159
No!

775
01:28:13.207 --> 01:28:15.793
You'll allow yourself to surrender. Mr. Murdoch.

776
01:28:15.918 --> 01:28:18.086
or it will result in this one's death. yes?

777
01:28:18.212 --> 01:28:22.090
What do I care? She's not my real wife!
She's nothing to me!

778
01:28:22.216 --> 01:28:26.345
But you do still care. don't you. Mr. Murdoch?

779
01:28:26.470 --> 01:28:31.099
You see. I have become the monster
you were intended to be.

780
01:28:32.893 --> 01:28:36.605
Shall I end her life now. as you would have?

781
01:28:40.067 --> 01:28:41.902
Don't hurt her. please!

782
01:28:42.027 --> 01:28:45.489
Then surrender. Mr. Murdoch.

783
01:28:46.990 --> 01:28:48.408
Sleep.

784
01:28:50.744 --> 01:28:52.412
Now.

785
01:28:54.331 --> 01:28:55.958
John?

786
01:29:11.014 --> 01:29:12.140
Sleep.

787
01:29:33.453 --> 01:29:36.874
The doctor was right. He has evolved.

788
01:29:36.999 --> 01:29:38.750
Kill him.

789
01:29:38.876 --> 01:29:41.253
Kill him! Kill him!

790
01:29:44.590 --> 01:29:47.259
Kill him! Kill him!

791
01:29:50.012 --> 01:29:52.514
He is powerful. yes.

792
01:29:52.639 --> 01:29:57.019
Dangerous. But he can also lead us to what we seek.

793
01:29:57.144 --> 01:30:00.439
What the doctor calls the soul.

794
01:30:00.564 --> 01:30:04.192
It is time for our experiment
to move into a final phase.

795
01:30:04.318 --> 01:30:06.945
We no longer need the other subjects.

796
01:30:07.070 --> 01:30:10.574
The time for study is over.

797
01:30:10.699 --> 01:30:15.495
It is time to be one with John Murdoch.

798
01:30:21.627 --> 01:30:24.963
It is time. Doctor. Imprint.

799
01:30:27.758 --> 01:30:30.510
Shut it down!

800
01:30:30.636 --> 01:30:33.180
Shut it down forever!

801
01:30:47.861 --> 01:30:49.863
What are you doing?

802
01:30:49.988 --> 01:30:54.451
They want to imprint you
with their own collective memories.

803
01:30:55.827 --> 01:31:01.083
They want to make you one of them.
so they can share your soul.

804
01:31:06.088 --> 01:31:08.382
Imprint. Doctor. No more disobedience.

805
01:31:08.507 --> 01:31:13.261
I'm sorry. John.
The pain will only last a moment.

806
01:31:15.472 --> 01:31:16.473
No!

807
01:31:24.606 --> 01:31:26.108
Remember. John.

808
01:31:27.401 --> 01:31:29.444
<i>You'll rise to greater heights than that. my boy.</i>

809
01:31:29.569 --> 01:31:32.114
<i>One day when you're older. you'll understand.</i>

810
01:31:32.990 --> 01:31:35.325
Remember.

811
01:31:35.450 --> 01:31:38.245
<i>That's it. John. Practice makes perfect.</i>

812
01:31:38.370 --> 01:31:41.456
<i>Now remember what I told you. Never talk to strangers.</i>

813
01:31:41.581 --> 01:31:43.208
John. remember.

814
01:31:43.333 --> 01:31:46.336
<i>You're probably wondering why I keep appearing in your memories.</i>

815
01:31:46.461 --> 01:31:48.797
<i>It is because I have inserted myself in them.</i>

816
01:31:48.922 --> 01:31:52.801
<i>All of these memories have been fabricated
to teach you about the Strangers.</i>

817
01:31:52.926 --> 01:31:55.804
<i>give you a lifetime of knowledge in a single syringe.</i>

818
01:31:58.765 --> 01:32:01.143
<i>You will survive. John.</i>

819
01:32:01.268 --> 01:32:05.355
<i>You will find strength within yourself. and you will prevail.</i>

820
01:32:05.480 --> 01:32:06.732
Remember.

821
01:32:07.649 --> 01:32:09.651
- <i>Hi. Uncle Karl.
- <i>Johnny!</i></i>

822
01:32:12.612 --> 01:32:14.740
<i>You're getting the hang of it. John.</i>

823
01:32:14.865 --> 01:32:16.742
<i>Maybe one day. I'll be working for you.</i>

824
01:32:17.701 --> 01:32:21.121
<i>This is the machine the Strangers use to amplify their thoughts.</i>

825
01:32:21.246 --> 01:32:24.332
<i>The machine that changes their world. You must take control of it.</i>

826
01:32:24.458 --> 01:32:26.376
<i>You must make the machine yours.</i>

827
01:32:26.501 --> 01:32:30.630
<i>I know you can beat them. John. But you must concentrate.</i>

828
01:32:32.924 --> 01:32:34.843
Something's wrong.

829
01:32:42.684 --> 01:32:46.772
<i>There is no time for romance. John. The world can be what you make it.</i>

830
01:32:47.814 --> 01:32:49.775
What have you done?

831
01:32:49.900 --> 01:32:54.780
<i>You have the power to make anything happen. but you must act now!</i>

832
01:37:38.521 --> 01:37:40.273
I knew you could do it. John.

833
01:37:40.398 --> 01:37:44.027
You have their power now. You control their machines.

834
01:37:44.152 --> 01:37:45.653
Where's Emma?

835
01:37:46.488 --> 01:37:50.658
She's not Emma anymore. John. She has been re-imprinted.

836
01:37:50.784 --> 01:37:52.952
- So give her back her memories.
- I can't.

837
01:37:53.078 --> 01:37:57.082
The facility where the Strangers stored
the memories has been destroyed.

838
01:37:57.916 --> 01:37:59.751
I'm sorry.

839
01:38:00.418 --> 01:38:02.879
What are you going to do now. John?

840
01:38:04.589 --> 01:38:07.717
You told me I had the power. didn't you?

841
01:38:08.510 --> 01:38:11.721
I can make these machines do anything I want.

842
01:38:12.806 --> 01:38:15.266
Make this world anything I want it to be.

843
01:38:16.142 --> 01:38:20.271
Just so long as I concentrate hard enough.

844
01:39:44.230 --> 01:39:46.232
Where are you going?

845
01:39:48.526 --> 01:39:49.986
Shell Beach.

846
01:40:30.902 --> 01:40:32.278
- What's the fare?
- Quarter.

847
01:40:38.535 --> 01:40:39.869
Oh. please.

848
01:40:39.994 --> 01:40:42.121
- Oh. no...
- It's fine.

849
01:40:42.247 --> 01:40:43.957
- Thank you.
- Okay.

850
01:41:23.705 --> 01:41:25.582
John...

851
01:41:29.294 --> 01:41:33.131
Been waiting for you. yes? What are you doing?

852
01:41:33.256 --> 01:41:36.217
I'm just making a few little changes around here. is all.

853
01:41:36.342 --> 01:41:41.139
- Are we sure that's what we want?
- I'm prepared to take my chances.

854
01:41:41.264 --> 01:41:45.810
I'm dying. John. Your imprint is not agreeable with my kind.

855
01:41:47.312 --> 01:41:52.358
But I wanted to know what it was like... how you feel.

856
01:41:52.483 --> 01:41:55.111
You know how I was supposed to feel.

857
01:41:55.236 --> 01:41:58.948
That person isn't me. Never was.

858
01:41:59.073 --> 01:42:02.702
You wanted to know what it was about us that made us human.

859
01:42:04.120 --> 01:42:07.624
Well. you're not going to find it in here.

860
01:42:09.125 --> 01:42:11.377
You went looking in the wrong place.

861
01:43:50.226 --> 01:43:52.103
It's so beautiful here.

862
01:43:57.316 --> 01:43:58.943
So bright.

863
01:44:04.949 --> 01:44:07.660
Do you know if Shell Beach is round here?

864
01:44:07.785 --> 01:44:10.121
I think that's it. just over there.

865
01:44:28.431 --> 01:44:30.475
I'm headed that way myself.

866
01:44:32.435 --> 01:44:34.479
Would you like to join me?

867
01:44:36.898 --> 01:44:38.649
Sure.

868
01:44:43.237 --> 01:44:44.989
I'm Anna. by the way.

869
01:44:45.865 --> 01:44:47.992
- What's your name?
- John.

870
01:44:50.328 --> 01:44:51.871
John Murdoch.
